snippet.title: America, Return to God - Barron Trump Sings
snippet.description:
America, Return to God

Check us out on Spotify! https://open.spotify.com/album/3y1CZVxPBVqYl2ljdNVWno?si=lLRWLYbeQcuXD9TQDeKi7A

⬇️⬇️⬇️ Watch more videos below! ⬇️⬇️⬇️
https://youtu.be/WBHJZs8ZeFQ
https://youtu.be/GAdihLnAiXk
https://youtu.be/SZZW8YMZlMg?si=kP7ZE5s5fhhjjpX2
https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=hq_JjAodbY0

Lyrics:
[Verse 1]
I walk these marble halls, see the flags on the wall,
Big dreams, big lights, but we’re feeling kinda small.
Freedom’s a song we all still sing,
But lately it’s missing a little something.

They taught me young, it ain’t all about gold,
It’s about the heart, it’s about the soul.
And somewhere between the noise and the news,
We forgot how to fill up the pews.

[Chorus]
America, it’s time to go to church again,
Hold your neighbor’s hand, say amen.
Get back to the love that built these shores,
The faith that opened all these doors.
Not just Sunday suits and old stained glass,
But a fire inside that’s built to last.
If we wanna rise, if we wanna mend,
America, it’s time to go to church again.

[Verse 2]
We got screens in our faces, dreams in our hands,
But peace don't come from a million plans.
It’s found in a prayer, a humble song,
Where broken hearts know they belong.

It’s not about who's right, who's wrong,
It’s about a place where we all belong.
Where mercy rains, and hope begins,
Where grace can heal our deepest sins.

[Chorus]
America, it’s time to go to church again,
Hold your neighbor’s hand, say amen.
Get back to the love that built these shores,
The faith that opened all these doors.
Not just Sunday suits and old stained glass,
But a fire inside that’s built to last.
If we wanna rise, if we wanna mend,
America, it’s time to go to church again.

[Bridge]
From small-town steeples to the city streets,
We need a little less pride, a little more knees.
It's not too late to turn it around,
The cross still stands on this hallowed ground.

[Final Chorus]
America, it’s time to go to church again,
Forgive like Him, love like friends.
Get back to the roots that made us strong,
Sing Amazing Grace all night long.
Not just words, not just pretend—
America, it’s time to go to church again.

[Outro]
Yeah, if we wanna heal, if we wanna win,
America… let’s go to church again.
